From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: V5 Project <v5@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 17:12:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] v5: drain generic rx burst

The V5 native LinuxCNC EtherCAT path uses IgH's generic PF_PACKET backend.
During the first OP-thread cycles, the master can receive a burst of state,
DC, mailbox, and process-data replies. The upstream generic backend polls only
10 frames per receive pass, which leaves valid replies queued until the master
has already timed out the datagrams; the same replies then arrive as
UNMATCHED.

Keep the LinuxCNC/IgH/lcec native motion path and only raise the generic
backend's receive drain budget so a startup burst is consumed in the same
cycle.
---
 devices/generic.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/devices/generic.c b/devices/generic.c
index 2222222..3333333 100644
--- a/devices/generic.c
+++ b/devices/generic.c
@@ -334,7 +334,7 @@ void ec_gen_device_poll(
     struct msghdr msg;
     struct sockaddr_ll addr;
     struct kvec iov;
-    int ret, budget = 10; // FIXME
+    int ret, budget = 128; // V5: drain startup/status bursts in one pass.
 
     if (dev->socket) {
         do {
